com.gwtplatform.mvp.client

Interface TabData

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TabDataBasic

    public interface TabData
    Classes of this type contains all the data required to create a new Tab. The default implementation is TabDataBasic but you can create your own class, with more information, if desired. See TabInfo for more details.
    Author:
    Philippe Beaudoin

    • Method Detail

      • getPriority

        float getPriority()
        A tab priority indicates where it should appear within the tab strip. In typical implementations of TabPanel, a tab with low priority will be placed more towards the left of the strip. Two tabs with the same priority will be placed in an arbitrary order.
        Returns:
        The priority.

      • getLabel

        String getLabel()
        Gets the label to display on the tab.
        Returns:
        The label.
